<key pageId="22" pageNumber="133">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,406,633]" pageId="22" pageNumber="133">
<keyLead pageId="22" pageNumber="133">
1 Tibia II with conspicuous brush of inclined long av erect black bristles in basal ½ (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1099,406,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 28" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[237,1339,196,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[237,1339,196,1789]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 28. Hercostomus setitibia sp. nov., male. (26) habitus: (27) antenna; (28) tibia II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376043/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="133">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
