<figureCitation box="[780,849,436,457]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="21.[151,250,991,1013]" captionTargetBox="[215,1384,221,939]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,970]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 29. Hercostomus setitibia sp. nov., male, hypopygium. Abbreviations: apv lobe: apicoventral epandrial lobe, bv lobe: basoventral epandrial lobe, cerc: cercus, dsur: dorsal surstylar lobe, hyp: hypandrium, pgo: postgonites, vsur: ventral surstylar lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376044/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="133">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) with basodorsal part reddish yellow and relatively small apv epandrial lobe. Cercus (
<figureCitation box="[453,522,465,486]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="21.[151,250,991,1013]" captionTargetBox="[215,1384,221,939]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,970]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 29. Hercostomus setitibia sp. nov., male, hypopygium. Abbreviations: apv lobe: apicoventral epandrial lobe, bv lobe: basoventral epandrial lobe, cerc: cercus, dsur: dorsal surstylar lobe, hyp: hypandrium, pgo: postgonites, vsur: ventral surstylar lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376044/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="133">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) rather narrow, with a slender apicodorsal process bearing three curved bristles.................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1113,494,515]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setitibia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[905,1113,494,515]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="133">Hercostomus setitibia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1119,1196,494,516]" pageId="22" pageNumber="133" rank="species">
